I have a P3-1ghz CPU, 1gb of RAM and a GF3-Ti500.. After loading SoL, my system would pause every 3 seconds for about half a second.. I was getting really really frustrated to say the least.. My disk was doing a lot of swapping and I really felt like my machine should be performing better then it was.. So I did some surfing and found this fix.. It links right to an MS article that in so many words says that all the extra RAM you have in your system is basically doing jack and @#%$ without this entry.. <br>
<br>
First, you set Windows to manage your Virtual Memory.. Secondly, add this line to your system.ini under the 386enh section as the directions say.. I zone substantially faster, the new textures load substantially faster and I have far far FAR less lag when I am in large groups of people that before dropped my framerate down to hideous rates.. Basically, this will make SoL run almost as fast as it did before the new engine in my honest opinion.. <br>
<br>
Give it a shot, it worked for me and has done great things for a number of my guildmates as well.. Its very worth it.. <br>
<br>
